  - var path = 'usvi'

block tweet
  a.tweet(href="https://ctt.ec/DidfP") Share

block content

  +territory(name, path, 'March 31, 1917', 'border')

  .intro
    p After Rear Admiral Summer E.W. Kitelle was sworn in as governor, he approached his chief of staff, William Russell White, about designing an official flag.
    p White tasked Percival W. Sparks, a yeoman and artist, with the design. Sparks took inspiration from the United States coat of arms and created a sketch. His wife Grace and her sister, Blanche Sasso, completed the flag’s embroidery.
    p The flag was officially adopted May 17, 1921.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Flag design
      p The flag of the U.S. Virgin Islands features a field of white charged with an eagle, centered and flanked by the letters, V and I.
      p Upon the eagle’s chest is a shield of blue with red and white stripes. In its talons are a sprig of laurel and three arrows.
      +survey(name, '37th')
    .visual.flag
      +flag(name, path, 'border')

  .guide.wide
    .content
      h2 Iconography
      ul.visual.icon-list
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-usvi-icon-eagle.svg', alt='an eagle superimposed with a shield')
          h4 eagle
          p freedom, strength, the United States
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-usvi-icon-laurel.svg', alt='sprig of laurel')
          h4 laurel
          p peace
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-usvi-icon-arrows.svg', alt='three arrows pointing upward')
          h4 3 arrows
          p strength, the islands of Saint Croix, Saint Thomas, and Saint John
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-usvi-icon-vi.svg', alt='the letters “V” and “I”')
          h4 VI
          p Virgin Islands

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Colors
      p U.S. Virgin Islands statute only specifies that the blue of the shield be the same as the blue from the U.S. national flag.
      p #[em The Flags and Anthems Manual] for the London 2012 Olympic Games does provide Pantone colors for the U.S. Virgin Islands flag, as specified here.
    .visual
      .colors.primary
        include includes/color-white-pantone
        .color
          .sample(class='yellow')
          .name Yellow
          .hex #fce300
          .pantone PMS 102
      .colors.secondary
        include includes/color-us-blue
        .color
          .sample(class='red')
          .name Red
          .hex #e03c31
          .pantone PMS 179
        .color
          .sample(class='azure')
          .name Azure
          .hex #69b3e7
          .pantone PMS 292
        .color
          .sample(class='green')
          .name Green
          .hex #009639
          .pantone PMS 355

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Construction
      p U.S. Virgin Islands statute does not specify dimensions or proportion for the flag.
      p It is commonly produced with a proportion of 2:3.
    .visual
      +construction(name, path)

